### Summary

Fixes #1071

On desktop screens, when the sidebar is expanded (`body.sidebar-active:not(.sidebar-collapsed)`), the `.hero-section` and `.hero-timeline-section` did not shift properly, causing content (hero text, CTAs, and the left side of the interactive roadmap) to slide behind and collide with the fixed sidebar.

### Root Cause

While `.projects-section` and `.footer` already had `padding-left` adjustments inside `@media (min-width: 1100px)`, the `.hero-section` and `.hero-timeline-section` were missing these rules entirely.

### Changes Made

**`web-app/css/styles.css`** — Added sidebar offset `padding-left` for both sections inside the existing `@media (min-width: 1100px)` block:

```css
body.sidebar-active:not(.sidebar-collapsed) .hero-section,
body.sidebar-active:not(.sidebar-collapsed) .hero-timeline-section {
  padding-left: 296px !important;
}

body.sidebar-collapsed .hero-section,
body.sidebar-collapsed .hero-timeline-section {
  padding-left: 128px !important;
}
